 🌿 Medicinal Plant Species Classification

A deep learning-powered image classification system for identifying medicinal plant species through leaf images. This project utilizes a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) architecture with MobileNetV2 as a feature extractor, delivering efficient and reliable predictions.

 📌 Project Highlights

- Preprocessing:Includes image rescaling, resizing, and augmentation techniques to improve model generalization.
- Model: Developed using TensorFlow and Keras, incorporating MobileNetV2 for lightweight, high-performance feature extraction.
- Accuracy: Achieved a test accuracy of 87.5%.
- Deployment: Integrated into an interactive Streamlit web application for easy, real-time plant species prediction.

 🎯 Objectives

- Automate the classification of medicinal plants using deep learning.
- Assist researchers, students, and professionals in identifying medicinal plants quickly and accurately.
- Showcase the practical application of lightweight deep learning models like MobileNetV2 in image classification tasks.

🚀 Features

- Real-time medicinal plant species prediction.
- Simple, clean, and responsive web interface using Streamlit.
- High classification accuracy with optimized model performance.
- Lightweight, mobile-friendly model architecture.

 🛠️ Technologies Used

- Python
- TensorFlow / Keras
- MobileNetV2
- Streamlit

